        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText></prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey></prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Based on the past NMA CO(1-0) observations, NGC 3628 has a velocity width of 90 km s^{-1} and the velocity resolution of 20.8 km s^{-1}.  We request a similar velocity resolution of 20.38 km s^{-1} in order to compare the results from the NMA.  We set up the rest frequency of CO(1-0) 115.27 GHz with bandwidth of 1875 MHz at velocity resolution of 20.38 km s^{-1} in baseband-1.  In order to subtract the continuum emission from CO(1-0), we set up the continuum in baseband-2 with frequency of 113.3962 GHz (=115.27-1.875) with the same bandwidth with CO(1-0) of 1875 MHz.  The continuum can reach rms level of 0.3 mJy beam^{-1}, and is enough for continuum subtraction. </prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Since the resolution of the NMA CO(1-0) observation is 3.0'' x 2.4'' (Tsai et al. 2012), we request the angular resolution beam size of 3'', which is similar to the NMA observation.  In order to cover the intense northern X-ray outflow, we set the field center at RA 11:20:16.15 and Dec 13:35:43.6 with position angle of 30 degree.  We need ACA in order to enhance the wide-field imaging capability.  We optimize the total number of pointings in 12m Array and ACA in order to get minimum pointing number but to cover maximum area of the X-ray outflow.  Thus we set the field size of 1.7 arcmin x 1.1 arcmin.  This requires 1.31 hours with 11 pointings for total 12m array time, and 5.22 hours with 5 pointings for total ACA time.  The estimated total time is 6.53 hours.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The expected noise level of weak diffuse emission from outflow area is estimated from our previous NMA observations.  The noise level of the NMA CO(1-0) channel maps is 4.9 mJy beam^{-1} with velocity resolution of 20.8 km s^{-1}.  We assume that the X-ray/CO(1-0) ratio is constant in the overall area of outflowing gas.  Thus, the CO(1-0) emission in large area should be 30% of the emission detected by the NMA.  This is corresponding to noise level of 1.8 mJy beam^{-1} with velocity resolution of 20.38 km s^{-1} and angular resolution of 3''x3'' for ALMA. 

</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
